%% CodeFlare Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / SDK
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant MCAD as MCAD Queue Controller<br/>(embedded in operator)
    participant InstaScale as InstaScale Controller<br/>(optional, embedded)
    participant MachineAPI as OpenShift Machine API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Cloud as Cloud Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over User,Cloud: Flow 1: AppWrapper Workload Scheduling

    User->>K8sAPI: Create AppWrapper CR<br/>Auth: User credentials
    K8sAPI->>MCAD: Watch event (AppWrapper created)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    MCAD->>MCAD: Evaluate scheduling policy,<br/>priority, quota
    MCAD->>K8sAPI: Create Pods/Deployments/Services<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>MCAD: Resources created

    Note over User,Cloud: Flow 2: InstaScale Auto-Scaling (when enabled)

    InstaScale->>K8sAPI: Watch AppWrappers<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>InstaScale: AppWrapper needs more compute
    InstaScale->>MachineAPI: Create MachineSets<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    MachineAPI->>Cloud: Provision new nodes<br/>Auth: Cloud credentials
    Cloud-->>MachineAPI: Nodes provisioned
    MachineAPI-->>InstaScale: MachineSets ready

    Note over User,Cloud: Flow 3: Operator Configuration Loading

    MCAD->>K8sAPI: GET/CREATE ConfigMap<br/>(codeflare-operator-config)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>MCAD: ConfigMap data<br/>(MCAD settings, InstaScale settings)
